hands_on_practices.solution:
We start from the Gell-Mann-Nishijima relation for each component of the $SU(2)_L$ doublet:
$$
Q \;=\; T_3 \;+\;\frac{Y}{2}\,.
$$
For the upper component $U'$ with $T_3=+\tfrac12$ and $Q_{U'}=+\tfrac{4}{3}$:
$$
\tfrac{4}{3} \;=\; \tfrac{1}{2} \;+\;\frac{Y}{2}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
\frac{Y}{2} \;=\;\tfrac{4}{3}-\tfrac{1}{2}
=\tfrac{8}{6}-\tfrac{3}{6}
=\tfrac{5}{6}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
Y=\tfrac{5}{3}.
$$
Consistency check for the lower component $D'$ with $T_3=-\tfrac12$ and $Q_{D'}=+\tfrac{1}{3}$:
$$
\tfrac{1}{3} \;=\; -\tfrac{1}{2}\;+\;\frac{Y}{2}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
\frac{Y}{2} \;=\;\tfrac{1}{3}+\tfrac{1}{2}
=\tfrac{2}{6}+\tfrac{3}{6}
=\tfrac{5}{6}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
Y=\tfrac{5}{3}.
$$
Thus the weak hypercharge of the new doublet is 
$$
Y=\frac{5}{3}.
$$
